gomodel:SYNGO_1967  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: CALEB-deficient mice display impaired synaptic function in juvenile but not adult synapses of the colliculus superior (Fig. 5). In particular, CALEB deficiency affect presynaptic properties at early developmental stages (Fig. 6).. Experimental description: \"Spontaneous Frequencies of EPSCs and IPSCs Are Reduced in CALEB-Deficient Mice at Early Postnatal but Not Mature Stages, while Synapse Numbers Remained Unchanged\", p. 239, legend to fig. 5" ;
